The teacher actively checks for understanding, moves around to assist learners, and incorporates timed activities to encourage efficiency. Learners also engage in peer marking, reinforcing self-assessment and accountability. Proper feedback is provided, ensuring clarity and continuous improvement. This approach balances teacher guidance with student-centered learning effectively.

Sentence examples also used to identify parts of speech, so Afr language skill is further cemented. Good checks for understanding by mixing up the number of tenses and questioning learners on those. PPT pres used to engage learners on subject matter. Learners given multiple opportunities to gain understanding of concepts before engaging in practical activity. Pushes learners to give accurate answers, as per Afr language prescriptions. Actively goes through every Q in the learning activity to ensure that learners understand what is required.
data.improvements: Teacher and learners use English widely during Afr lesson. Not sure that he knows learner names as he refers to 'there at the back' when wanting to call a learner. No links shared, between current learning and previous learning and background knowledge. No leadership roles identified. Learners not placed in learning groups.
